Document_summary: This document is an application by Hawaiian Electric Company seeking approval for a Power Purchase Agreement with Waiawa PV, LLC for a solar project in Hawaii. The document outlines the project details, requested approvals, and financial impacts. The implications are that the project aligns with Hawaii's energy policy goals and renewable energy objectives, with a focus on cost-effective and clean energy services.

The document is an application for approval of a Power Purchase Agreement between Hawaiian Electric Company, Inc. and Kalaeloa Solar Two, LLC. It outlines the terms and conditions of the agreement, including the construction and operation of a 5 MW photovoltaic energy facility in Kalaeloa, Hawaii. The document also discusses interconnection facilities, competitive bidding for renewable energy, and Hawaii's energy policy goals.
